      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/160/5680",
      "text": [
        " : \"أَيُّمَا رَجُلٍ أَقَرَّ بِوَلَدِهِ ثُمَّ اِنْتَفَى مِنْهُ فَلَيْسَ لَهُ ذَلِكَ وَ لاَ كَرَامَةَ يُلْحَقُ بِهِ وَلَدُهُ إِذَا كَانَ مِنِ اِمْرَأَتِهِ أَوْ وَلِيدَتِهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5680 - Hammad narrated from Al-Halabi, from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"Any man who acknowledges his child and then later denies him has no right to do so, and he deserves no respect.\nHis child will be attributed to him if the child is from his wife or his maidservant.\""
        ]
      }
    },
